# Deep Dive Review: Noise Survey Analysis Dashboard

**Date:** 2026-05-05  
**Scope:** Full-stack review of the Noise Survey Analysis Bokeh dashboard — JavaScript frontend, Python backend, UI/UX, tests, and data analysis workflows.  
**Method:** Static code analysis, architecture pattern review, bug pattern search, test coverage assessment, and feature gap identification against professional acoustic consultancy workflows.

---

## Executive Summary

The project is a sophisticated, performant Bokeh-based noise survey dashboard with a well-architected Redux-style frontend and a hybrid static/live server backend. However, **production reliability is being undermined by a category of defensive-coding gaps**, stale debug instrumentation left in production code, event listener memory leaks, and several UI/UX friction points that slow down expert data review. There are also **genuinely useful analysis features missing** that would materially improve reporting workflows.

This review prioritizes fixes and features by **impact-to-effort ratio** and **risk to data integrity / user trust**.

